# 🎯 Executive Overview

0day was a Linux machine that initially appeared fairly simple, exposing only SSH and HTTP services. Enumeration quickly revealed several interesting web directories, including a backup location containing an encrypted RSA private key.

At first, the backup key looked like the intended route for gaining access. I spent time cracking the key passphrase and attempting SSH authentication, but that path ultimately led nowhere.

After stepping back and performing deeper enumeration, I discovered a vulnerable CGI endpoint susceptible to Shellshock (CVE-2014-6271). Exploiting this vulnerability provided remote code execution as `www-data`, which allowed me to obtain the user flag.

Privilege escalation was achieved through a vulnerable Linux kernel using an OverlayFS local privilege escalation exploit, resulting in full root access.

