# ❌ What Didn't Work

One of the most valuable parts of this machine was learning which paths were misleading.

| Attempt                          | Why It Looked Promising               | Why It Failed                   | Lesson                                       |
| -------------------------------- | ------------------------------------- | ------------------------------- | -------------------------------------------- |
| Using the RSA key directly       | Private keys often lead to SSH access | Passphrase required             | Keys may be encrypted                        |
| Guessing user `0day`             | Homepage referenced 0day              | Authentication failed           | Don't rely on assumptions                    |
| Using user `ryan` with key       | Only discovered user account          | Authentication failed           | Correct user doesn't guarantee access        |
| Treating cracked key as foothold | Passphrase successfully recovered     | SSH authentication still failed | Cracked credentials aren't always sufficient |
| Running exploit source directly  | Downloaded exploit code               | Forgot to compile first         | Always verify file type before execution     |

