# 💡 Breakthrough Moment

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The RSA key appeared to be the intended attack path, but after multiple failed SSH attempts I decided to reassess the machine. Running Nikto revealed additional information about the web server and led me back toward the CGI functionality. That shift in thinking ultimately uncovered the real vulnerability: Shellshock.

