# 🏁 Conclusion

0day was an excellent example of how a machine can intentionally present misleading attack paths while rewarding thorough enumeration.

The encrypted RSA key initially appeared to be the intended route into the system. After spending time cracking the passphrase and testing SSH authentication, it became clear that another path needed to be explored.

Further enumeration uncovered a vulnerable CGI endpoint susceptible to Shellshock, which provided initial access as `www-data`. From there, kernel enumeration identified a vulnerable OverlayFS implementation, leading to full root compromise.

The biggest takeaway from this room was the importance of persistence and methodology. A promising lead should never stop further enumeration, because the real vulnerability may be hiding elsewhere.

